    • Method Detail

      • openInputFile

        public static java.io.File openInputFile​(java.util.Scanner kb)
        The openInputFile prompts the user for a filename. After the user enters the filename, an new file object is created. The file object is checked to see if the file actually exists. If the file exists it is returned otherwise the user is reprompted to enter a file name. This occurs until a file is found that exists.
        Parameters:
        kb - Representing a valid Scanner object
        Returns:
        File Representing a File that exists
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if kb is null
        NOTE:
        The input buffer will be left empty
